@ From the client:
@ First of all thanks for the loadimage3.jar. This allowed us to run the
@ simulation exhaustively. Which also allowed us to experiment and get down to
@ the root of the problem. I hope I explain this correctly.
@ .
@ Our hosts are configured to talk to each other in jumbo frame packet sizes 
@ of I think 9k. Our load balancer does not support jumbo frames and it runs at 
@ a packet size of 1.5k. So any traffic coming from a different subnet was fine
@ because it all used the default packet  size. But when a request was given 
@ from within the same subnet it was requesting 9k packet sizes. The load 
@ balancer was not able to process them hence the timeouts and other issues. 
@ The
@ intermittent problem arose from the fact that some of the sig files are 
@ smaller than others. So sometimes it was able to negotiate a packet size that 
@ worked.
@ .
@ Thanks for all the help and frustration sharing.
@ Closing bug as it is a problem with the load balancer.
          
