Cause
The Java class file created by the JSP compiler is corrupted.

Fix
If you see an error message like this: java.lang.ClassFormatError: (Truncated class file)
that means that the Java class file created by the JSP compiler is  corrupted.
The workaround for this problem is to simply change the timestamp of the JSP
file that is referred by the URL. You can do that by opening the file,  adding an empty
line at the end of the file and saving the file again (on UNIX  @ platforms you can simply
"touch" the file). The JSP will be recompiled the next time it is invoked and the problem
will be fixed.
