468494.1 Options to clean up WF_DEFERRED AQ Agent
============================================================================== 
3)Recreating WF_DEFERRED AQ Agent 

Recreating WF_DEFERRED is seen as being more efficient and faster than using wfevqcln.sql option 
with the end result being same. Additionally, recreating the queue will save on the tablespace and hence WF and Performance Development recommend this option. 
The downside of it is that some downtime is required in order to drop and recreate the queue. 
This method consists of three major steps as, 
Backup events,
Recreate WF_DEFERRED AQ and Re-Enqueue the events 

i)BACKUP: Use $FND_TOP/sql/wfaqback.sql script to Backup WF_DEFERRED AQ before attempting to recreate the queue. 
wfaqback.sql backs up a given Workflow Advanced Queue (of WF_EVENT_T payload) for a list of given event names. 
The event messages are stored in an intermediate table. Once the queue in question is recreated, the events can be re-enqueued on to the queue using wfaqrenq.sql 
which will take the messages from the intermediate table and re-equeue them. 
Bug << 6530012>>  is open at the time of writing this document (26/11/07) for an issue whereby this script was not backing up events in status WAIT. See Note << 464579.1 >> for the workaround to this problem. 

USAGE 
sqlplus apps/<apps pwd> @wfaqback.sql <Agent Name> 
For Example: 
sqlplus apps/<apps pwd> @wfaqback.sql WF_DEFERRED 

IMPORTANT NOTE 
Please note that the user needs to open this script using a text pad and specify the list of event messages that are *NOT* to be backed up in list "l_unwanted_events". The messages specified in this list will not be backed up for re-enqueueing later using wfaqrenq.sql. 
If % is specified in the list, it means that all the events are to be removed from the queue and none is required to be backed up. This is same as recreating the queue without backing up events. 

ii)Dropping and Recreating WF_DEFERRED AQ Agent 
Web-tier and Concurrent-tier should be down when recreating WF_DEFERRED. 
Stop the complete middle tier, Web, CP and Forms to ensure there is no one using applications that could 
cause Business Event System activity. 

a) Query and note tablespace that is currently used by CORRID index for WF_DEFERRED with: 
select index_name, tablespace_name from all_indexes where index_name = 'WF_DEFERRED_N1'; 
INDEX_NAME                     TABLESPACE_NAME
------------------------------ ------------------------------
WF_DEFERRED_N1                 APPLSYSX


b) Drop WF_DEFERRED AQ using $FND_TOP/patch/115/sql/wfevqued.sql script. 
If the customer does not have this script, it could be obtained from Patch << 4334965 >> - ATG.RUP3 or above 

USAGE 
sqlplus apps/appspwd @wfevqued.sql APPLSYS APPLSYSPWD <Agent Name> 

For Example: 
sqlplus apps/<apps_schema_pwd> @wfevqued.sql APPLSYS <applsyspwd> WF_DEFERRED 

c) Recreate WF_DEFERRED AQ using $FND_TOP/patch/115/sql/wfevquc2.sql script 
USAGE 
sqlplus apps/pwd @wfevquc2.sql APPLSYS APPLSYSPWD <qname> APPS <retry> <delay> <retention> 

For Example: 
sqlplus apps/<apps_schema_passwd> @$FND_TOP/patch/115/sql/wfevquc2.sql APPLSYS 
<applsys_schema_passwd> WF_DEFERRED APPS 5 3600 86400 

d) Create subscribers 
sqlplus apps/<apps_schema_passwd> @$FND_TOP/patch/115/sql/wfbesqsubc.sql APPLSYS <applsys_schema_passwd> 

e) Create index on CORRID 
sqlplus apps/<apps_schema_passwd> @$FND_TOP/patch/115/sql/wfbesqidxc.sql APPLSYS 
<applsys_schema_passwd> <aq index tablespace noted in (ii)(a)> 

iii)Re-Enqueuing: Re-enqueue messages back from temporary table to WF_DEFERRED AQ with wfaqrenq.sql script 

This script re-enqueues messages that are backed up by wfaqback.sql script. 
wfaqback.sql creates a WF_QUEUE_TEMP_TABLE and backs up the specified event messages. Wfaqrenq.sql script takes the messages from the TEMP table and re-enqueues them to the Agent. 
It Supports messages of WF_EVENT_T type. 

USAGE 
sqlplus apps/<apps_schema_passwd> $FND_TOP/sql/wfaqrenq.sql WF_DEFERRED 

iv)Run afwfqgnt.sql to recreate grants/synonyms for Workflow Advanced Queue tables 
sqlplus apps/apps @$FND_TOP/patch/115/sql/afwfqgnt.sql APPS <APPS PWD> APPLSYS <APPLSYS PWD> 
v)Verify Message counts within temp table and WF_DEFERRED when re-equeing is completed.

