 The difference in the cookie persistence is explained best by the following:
    
    1) A URL that load-balances between multiple MTs in an HTTP pool require active-insert cookie
    peristence. This ensures that sessions remain in place when balancing between more than one MT.
    This would explain why you are seeing the cookie info from erptest.integra-ls.com.
    
    2) A URL that only has one MT in the HTTP pool requires no load-balancing, as there is only one MT
    that the VIP is handing off to...if that makes sense. There are no additional peer MTs to load
    balance between, so there is no cookie persistence set via "active-insert." This setup has been
    used as a setup guideline for all our customers, and being such, you can exclude this
    configuration as a source of your problem.
    
    The difference between the two URL persistence settings are in-place by design/configuration, and
    changing one to resemble the other is not the fix for your issue.
    
