Generic Note
------------
   UNPUBLISHED..

There are a lot of reasons why data wouldn't purge.  Its not always easy to get rid if it.

There are several options but you have to figure out what is keeping the data from purging in the first place.  The most common problem is that there is either a child or parent process open or an open notification.

There isn't any one fix because of the differing reasons the data may not purge.

WF item is eligible for purging only if the following query is satisfied: .

select 'Eligible'
from wf_items wfi
where wfi.item_type = <item_type> and wfi.item_key = <item key> and wfi.end_date < sysdate - <Age> and not exists( SELECT null FROM WF_ITEMS WI WHERE END_DATE IS NULL START WITH WI.ITEM_TYPE = wfi.item_type AND WI.ITEM_KEY = wfi.item_key CONNECT BY PRIOR WI.ITEM_TYPE = WI.PARENT_ITEM_TYPE AND PRIOR WI.ITEM_KEY = WI.PARENT_ITEM_KEY) and not exists( (SELECT null FROM WF_ITEMS WI WHERE END_DATE IS NULL START WITH WI.ITEM_TYPE = wfi.item_type AND WI.ITEM_KEY = wfi.item_key CONNECT BY PRIOR WI.PARENT_ITEM_TYPE = WI.ITEM_TYPE AND PRIOR WI.PARENT_ITEM_KEY = WI.ITEM_KEY) .

In other words, to get purged, a (closed) workflow item must not have any open (direct or indirect) child or parent flows (workflow items).   In the cases you uploaded the parent workflows are still OPEN ie no enddate.


What I generally do in these cases is start with an example of a process that is not purging.

I usually take the item_type and item_key and run
$FND_TOP/sql/wfstat.sql <item_type> <item_key>

This should tell you if you have any open actions or notifications.

There are several ways to get rid of them you just have to be sure you are getting the correct data.

Here are some options.

First choice abort via OAM... then purge.

Here is an example wferror item_type.


1. Login to OAM >Workflow Manager

2. At the bottom of the page on the right side

Under Throughput >select Work Items

3. At the top on the right ---> View : Select Errored Work Items --->Go

4. You well see a number of notifications for example 1-25 Select Next
You will need to go to your last page -- as your errored items may vary.

On this page I see System Error

5. Select the link ...
It takes you to a page with two Work Item Activity Stages

DEFAULT_ERROR

and

RESET_ERROR


6. Click the one I want to get rid of ...

And select ABORT All

7. Once Complete you can run the Purge Obsolete Runtime Data to get rid of the now Closed out notifications.

Note:  This will Abort the WFERROR process completely so make sure you really do not want these errored notifications  before completing the above steps.


