miko notification close

If its something simple like just an open notification you can close them with a script also.


Run something like this from sqlplus.

spool closenotif.sql

select 'exec WF_NOTIFICATION.CLOSE('''||Notification_id||''');'
from wf_notifications
Where status='OPEN'
and mail_status='MAIL'
and message_type = 'WFERROR'


spool off

This will generate output that can be saved (closenotif.sql) and ran like a
script....for example..the file contains..


exec WF_NOTIFICATION.CLOSE('875326');
exec WF_NOTIFICATION.CLOSE('877361');

Make sure it contains the notification you want closed.. the script will list ALL OPEN/to be MAILED WFERROR notifications so be sure to add conditional statements to the where clause to narrow the notifications to close.  Note reponse notifications cannot be simply closed you will have to abort those processes that contain response notifications.

SO the bottom line is there is no easy fix... the software was designed not to remove anything that wasnt fully completed.

I would start with the wferror processes as that will free up a lot of the other processes and work from there.
