"How To Remove a Column From Audit Trial Tables? (Doc ID 383053.1)"


The plan as in the note is: 

$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$

1- Open the application with responsibility

   System Administrator -> Security -> AuditTrail ->Groups

2- Query the group that contains the table that you want to modify columns assignment

3- Disable this group using the option : Disable - Purge Table

4- Run the concurrent request "AuditTrail Update Tables"


5- Manually clean remaining AuditTrial data related to the same table as the following:

        A. Drop triggers <table_NAME>_ai, ad, au

        B. Drop procedures <table_name>_aip, aup, adp

        C. Drop views <table_name>_ac1, av1

        D. Delete any synonyms for this table returned the following selects:

    select owner, object_type, object_name from dba_objects where object_name like '%_A';

    select table_owner, synonym_name from user_synonyms where synonym_name like '%_A';
    

    Only delete the data items above and not the entire table.

    For concerns on specific product data,please consult with the associated product team for 
guidance on them.
    

6- Take backup of the following table "FND_AUDIT_COLUMNS" as the following:

   create table FND_AUDIT_COLUMNS_BKP as select * from FND_AUDIT_COLUMNS

7- Go to the following navigation path : System Administrator -> Security -> AuditTrail 
-> Tables
8- Query your table that you need to remove a column from it.

9- Go to Help -> Diagnostics -> Examine <Enter apps password>

10- Choose the feild = COLUMN_ID and take remark of that value

11- Choose the feild = TABLE_ID and take remark of that value too.

12- Log in to sqlplus using apps/<apps password>
13- Execute the following:

    delete from FND_AUDIT_COLUMNS where TABLE_ID = <value in step 10> and column_id = 
<value in step 9>;
14- commit;

15- Go to the following navigation path: System Administrator -> Security -> AuditTrail 
-> Groups
16- Query the group that contains the table that you made the columns change

17- Enable this group using the option : Enabled

18- Run the concurrent request "AuditTrail Update Tables"

$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$

