SR 3-6377953331: Oracle R12 Applet not signed

Dear customer,
I analysed your updates below and I believe its expected behaviour, not the bug.
As mentioned in 1207184.1
Oracle E-Business Suite uses a self-signed certificate to sign the JAR files that are downloaded to the client PC when launching forms and other applets (such as Workflow Status Diagram or Account Hierarchy Manager).  This results in the popup of a warning - as shown in the example below - that requires the user to make a decision on whether to run the application and if they should "Always trust content from this publisher".  Security conscious users may be concerned about accepting this certificate.
Which cause the initial message

"Warning Security 
The applications digital certificate cannot be verified."

If you explain to users this message, and "Always trust content from this publisher" check box will be switched during first start of forms, the message should no longer be display.

Second possibility is to "CA signed Certificate" instead of  "Self-signed certificate" 
The security is same here, only the message is changed to 

"Warning Security 
The application's digital certificate has been verified."

The difference is only if users trust certificate signed "only by your company" or  "CA signed Certificate".
We are still speaking about certificate used for forms, which is the "inside communication", after logging to EBSO.
EBSO URL is signed by "CA signed Certificate".
So the gain here is not significant and most or OnDemand customers is using    "Self-signed certificate"  on this layer   

