All
I am sharing an issue which Ajay Deshpande recently identified which ought to help when encountering EBS FS_CLONE hanging. 
Please share with your teams. 
Please feel free to pass on to anyone else who may find this useful.
fs_clone hang issue :

Ref: (Doc ID 1644660.1)

Technipnet:3-5LQ8YQ1

Genpact:
SR: 3-12305627061 RFC: 3-5MUV5N5

We have seen cases when fs_clone seems to run/hang. If you check the log files you can see java heap failures during WLS domain unpack operation but  
for some reason this failure/error is not propagated back to main fs_clone process and it just stays in hanging status. 
	This is more likely to happen  in environments where we have more numbers of manages servers as FMW clone needs more memory for unpacking operation.

We have identified two such environments :Technipnet and Genpact
We need to implement following  as part of PA/PMP /CM/Refresh to make more memory available to java heap for fs_clone operation. it will also reduce the fs_clone runtime.


1.       Edit $CONTEXT_FILES on all MTs
  From
  =====
  <enable_t2p_config_jvm_args oa_var="s_enable_t2p_config_jvm_args" osd="UNIX">#</enable_t2p_config_jvm_args>

TO
  ==
  <enable_t2p_config_jvm_args oa_var="s_enable_t2p_config_jvm_args" osd="UNIX"></enable_t2p_config_jvm_args>

2.       Check this variable is set to at least to this value:
s_t2p_config_jvm_args">-Xms512m -Xmx1024m</t2p_config_jvm_args>  "you can push it to 2gb based on available memory in environment.

3.       Run autoconfig


if the issue persists change to 
	export CONFIG_JVM_ARGS="-Xms1024m -Xmx2048m"


If you are facing the hang  when above is not set, you can kill the existing fs_clone run and rerun it with force option after implementing the above plan.
Thanks to Ajay for seeing this through.
