Hi SME/TECH guys&gals,

just FYI - i have recently had a third case where the OVM for Dom0 upgrade was executed and afterwards the RAC ceased to function.

First was with American Airlines TAEA2I - they have 4 nodes, 2 were okay, 2 dead. 
Turns out during the OVM upgrade they did not correctly setup the ethernet bridge for the interconnect between the two dom0, 
which are hosting the DB nodes. Result is - the other nodes on the another dom0 will never come up because they know via voting disk the cluster is already up, 
however cant reach the other nodes via interconnect. Took me a while to jump between teams to get someone capable of understanding how to fix it. 
(first, i thought the problem is at the VLAN config - wrong tag or sth)..
Today i have encountered another one...

