vmohsfnacxl014 for Apache and Forms

It's critical that you don't attempt any service restoration to primary nodes. Please first ask to customer if they are still experiencing the outage. PFNA2I is designed to automatically failover from primary to secondary nodes at the mentioned component levels (DB, CM and Apache/Forms). If the customer is already runing on secondary nodes and you try to get them back to primary nodes, you might actually cause a second outage for customer and a bigger impact. After the critical business hours we must have a customer approved RFC to bring a failed DB back online. Testing showed that this could be done with no customer impact, but in production this did cause disruption, so it should be done at a non-critical time when if issues occur then the CM could be bounced.

Customer specific SPECIAL FAILOVER HANDLING INSTRUCTIONS

PFNA2I instance is configured with ACTIVE-PASSIVE Cluster Configuration for Concurrent Processing.

ACTIVE Node : vmohsfnacxl012 - auohsfnacxd03

PASSIVE Node : vmohsfnacxl015 - auohsfnacxd04

In the ACTIVE-PASSIVE Cluster configuration, when any one of the cluster Node (meaning, if active node DB or Concurrent Node is stopped ; or Passive DB or Concurrent node is stopped) is stopped due to issues, this application is configured to run safely. EBSO Application itself will fail-over to the available node.

If any of the ACTIVE-PASSIVE Node is stopped (ACTVIE Nodes: vmohsfnacxl012 and auohsfnacxd03, PASSIVE Nodes: vmohsfnacxl015 - auohsfnacxd04) please dont start the stopped node until it SDM confirms to start the stopped node(s). Check the status of Concurrent Manager processes in the running PCP server (Maximum wait for 15 min so that PCP can move from Active node to Passive node), normally the Concurrent processes does get moved from active node to passive node, but in our observation once we saw a lock (lock mentioned in the ICM/concurrent log file) was preventing the Concurrent movement. When we see any locking holding Concurrent process movement from Active node to passive node ( ICM/concurrent log file will have the lock error) please kill the locked Database session for the smooth movement of Concurrent processes from Active node to passive node.

If ALL ACTIVE-PASSIVE NODES are stopped, then please go-ahead and start the application with or without SDM confirmation.

