Exalogic VM Architecture limitation -- Start

*********************************************

As per OD standards we need to make sure to mount MT node's <sid>/applcsf and <sid>/oratmp to DB node. In Exalogic VM, we cant mount any Exalogic VM specific storage out side of Exalogic Rack.

Since we need to make sure to mount <sid>/applcsf and <sid>/oratmp in both Exadata and Exalogic nodes, we have NOT used the storage attached with Exalogic VM servers, Instead we have used our regular ZFS/NFS file system as <sid>/applcsf and <sid>/oratmp.

Hence when we do any activities (refresh and so on) which relates to <sid>/applcsf and <sid>/oratmp , we need to make sure to include the ZFS/NFS <sid>/applcsf and <sid>/oratmp.** Please give additional focus on this

OD standarf backup script can take the backup of all the mount points, we have worked with backup team to make the required changes in the script for this.

