Single Sign-On (SSO) Solution Responsibilities

The overall TechnipFMC SSO solution is owned by TechnipFMC, 
however OMCS/ACS is responsible for the EBS and OID elements of the SSO solution.

OMCS/ACS is NOT responsible for:

1. TechnipFMC�s PingFederate system,

2. TechnipFMC�s Active Directory system,

3. The interface between EBS and the PingFederate Agent residing in EBS.

Login Check To Be Performed by TechnipFMC:
If TechnipFMC suspects they cannot login using SSO, then TechnipFMC must:
1. First test the EBS SSO urls for both their private and public EBS URLs
2. Then test the �local� login EBS URL (for both the private and public EBS URLs) to determine if potential EBS system down issues
3. If an SSO login issue (item 2 works, but item 1 fails), then TechnipFMC should first check a) PingFederate, b) AD and c) their network.
4. If the issue is determined to be EBS or OID related then TechnipFMC should raise an appropriate SR with ACS/OMCS to check EBS and OID.

OMCS SSO checks, for TTNPNI:
1. Check if you can login to EBS via SSO using the "OMCS" SSO test account for both the private and public EBS URLs - The password for "OMCS" SSO test account is in OMP.
2. Check if you can login using the "local" non SSO URLs to EBS, with both the private and public URLs with the standard sysadmin account.  This will confirm if there is an EBS outage.
3. Check if you can login to EBS production PTNPNI as above. There is a separate OID, EBS, and PingFederate system for PTNPNI.  But, TechnipFMC Active Directory system is shared across PROD (PTNPNI) and non-production (TTNPNI and DTNPNI) and also there is some shared network components.

User Creation:
For OID, TechnipFMC is responsible for user creation in their Active Directory system, and/or OID.  User creation/maintenance is a functional type item within OID.  If there is a user creation issue (e.g. Dipsync interface between AD to OID), TechnipFMC are able to review OID and Dipsync logs via a read only operating system user account for OID, and also check data via the OID front end application user customer administrator functionality.  TechnipFMC should check via front end and logs first before raising SR with OMCS to investigate an issue in this area.

Load Balancer

The Load Balancer is implemented and managed by TechnipFMC and their 3rd-party implementer. Any issues with the Load Balancer should be referred to TechnipFMC.

SSL Certificates

The SSL Certificates are implemented and managed by TechnipFMC and their 3rd-party implementer. Any issues with the SSL Certificates should be referred to TechnipFMC.
